{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:21:48.864Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradients"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are the cornerstone of machine learning optimization—a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vector containing all partial derivatives"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of a multivariable function that points in the direction of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "steepest ascent"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". The gradient tells you exactly how to adjust all parameters (weights, biases) simultaneously to either increase or decrease the function's output, making it the engine of gradient descent and backpropagation in neural networks."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Gradients — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical definition:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a function "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "f(x₁, x₂,..., xₙ)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with multiple inputs, the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "gradient"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "∇f = (∂f/∂x₁, ∂f/∂x₂, ..., ∂f/∂xₙ)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Notation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The symbol "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "∇"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (called \"nabla\" or \"del\") represents the gradient operator."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In simpler terms: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "The gradient is just a vector of all partial derivatives"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Geometric interpretation:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Imagine standing on a 3D hill (the function surface):\n\n         z\n         |\n         |     / ← Hill surface z = f(x, y)\n         |    /\n         |___/______ x\n        /\n       y\n\nThe gradient ∇f at your position:\n- Points in direction of steepest UPHILL climb [web:169][web:171]\n- Magnitude = steepness of the hill [web:173]\n- Negative gradient -∇f points in steepest DOWNHILL direction [web:169][web:174]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hiking analogy"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": If you're climbing a mountain and want to reach the peak fastest, follow the gradient. If you want to descend to the valley (minimize loss), follow the negative gradient."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key properties:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Points uphill"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "∇f points toward steepest increase"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Negative points downhill"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "-∇f points toward steepest decrease"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Magnitude = steepness"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "∇f"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "= rate of fastest increase"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Perpendicular to contours"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "∇f is perpendicular to level curves/surfaces"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters — Importance in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradients are the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "engine of machine learning optimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "AI Component"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How gradients apply"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient Descent"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Update: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "w = w - learning_rate × ∇L"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (follow negative gradient downhill)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backpropagation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compute gradients through neural network layer-by-layer"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss Minimization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient tells direction to reduce error"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Parameter Updates"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each weight update guided by ∂L/∂w (component of gradient)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Find minima by following -∇L to bottom of valley"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": In training GPT-4 with billions of parameters, the gradient ∇L has billions of components, each telling one weight how to change to reduce loss."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits — Key advantages"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Multi-variable direction"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Tells you how to change ALL parameters simultaneously"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Steepest path"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Points in direction of fastest increase/decrease"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimization guide"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Enables systematic minimization via gradient descent"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Efficient learning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Single gradient computation guides all parameter updates"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convergence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Gradient magnitude → 0 signals optimal solution"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs — Downsides and limitations"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-off"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Impact"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Local information"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient only knows about nearby landscape (can get stuck in local minima)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Computational cost"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Computing gradients for millions/billions of parameters is expensive"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient issues"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Can explode (too large) or vanish (too small) in deep networks"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Non-convex functions"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Multiple local minima → may not find global optimum"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works — Step-by-step computation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "From partial derivatives to gradient:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Function: f(x, y) = x² + xy + y³\n\n# Step 1: Compute partial derivatives\n∂f/∂x = 2x + y\n∂f/∂y = x + 3y²\n\n# Step 2: Assemble into gradient vector\n∇f = [∂f/∂x, ∂f/∂y] = [2x + y, x + 3y²]\n\n# Step 3: Evaluate at point (1, 2)\n∇f(1, 2) = [2×1 + 2, 1 + 3×2²] = [4, 13]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Gradient at (1, 2) is — points uphill, steepest direction"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python implementations:"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SymPy (symbolic):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import sympy as sp\n\nx, y = sp.symbols('x y')\nf = x**2 + x*y + y**3\n\n# Gradient = vector of partials\ngradient = [sp.diff(f, x), sp.diff(f, y)]\n# [2*x + y, x + 3*y**2]\n\n# Evaluate at (1, 2)\ngradient_at_point = [g.subs({x: 1, y: 2}) for g in gradient]\n# [4, 13]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NumPy (numerical):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef f(x, y):\n    return x**2 + x*y + y**3\n\n# Compute gradient at point (1, 2)\nh = 1e-5\ndf_dx = (f(1 + h, 2) - f(1, 2)) / h  # ≈ 4\ndf_dy = (f(1, 2 + h) - f(1, 2)) / h  # ≈ 13\n\ngradient = np.array([df_dx, df_dy])\nprint(f\"∇f(1, 2) ≈ {gradient}\")  # [4, 13]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 4}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch (autograd):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\nx = torch.tensor([1.0, 2.0], requires_grad=True)\ny = x[0]**2 + x[0]*x [codesignal](https://codesignal.com/learn/courses/advanced-calculus-for-machine-learning/lessons/understanding-gradient) + x [codesignal](https://codesignal.com/learn/courses/advanced-calculus-for-machine-learning/lessons/understanding-gradient)**3\n\n# Compute gradient\ny.backward()\n\nprint(f\"Gradient: {x.grad}\")  # [4, 13]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to use gradients — Gradient Descent"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The algorithm:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Initialize parameters randomly\nw = random_initialization\n\n# Iterate\nfor iteration in range(num_iterations):\n    # Step 1: Compute gradient ∇L(w)\n    gradient = compute_gradient(loss, w)\n    \n    # Step 2: Update in negative gradient direction (downhill!)\n    w = w - learning_rate * gradient\n    \n    # Step 3: Check convergence\n    if np.linalg.norm(gradient) < threshold:\n        break  # Gradient ≈ 0 → reached minimum"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why negative gradient?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " Gradient points UPHILL; we want DOWNHILL to minimize loss, so multiply by -1."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example: Minimizing f(x) = x²"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Function to minimize\ndef f(x):\n    return x**2\n\n# Gradient: f'(x) = 2x (single variable, gradient = derivative)\ndef gradient(x):\n    return 2*x\n\n# Gradient descent\nx = 5.0  # Start at x = 5\nlearning_rate = 0.1\n\nfor i in range(100):\n    grad = gradient(x)\n    x = x - learning_rate * grad\n    \n    if i % 20 == 0:\n        print(f\"Iteration {i}: x = {x:.4f}, f(x) = {f(x):.4f}\")\n\nprint(f\"Final: x = {x:.6f}, f(x) = {f(x):.6f}\")  # x ≈ 0, f(x) ≈ 0"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Updates"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "x = 5 → x = 5 - 0.1×10 = 4.0\nx = 4 → x = 4 - 0.1×8 = 3.2\nx = 3.2 → x = 3.2 - 0.1×6.4 = 2.56\n...\nx → 0 (minimum)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key relationships — Connecting concepts"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Derivative → Partial → Gradient:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single variable: f'(x) = derivative (slope)\nMultiple variables: ∂f/∂x, ∂f/∂y = partial derivatives (slopes in each direction)\nAll partials combined: ∇f = [∂f/∂x, ∂f/∂y] = gradient (vector of steepest direction)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In neural networks:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss L(w₁, w₂, ..., wₙ) with n weights\n\nGradient: ∇L = [∂L/∂w₁, ∂L/∂w₂, ..., ∂L/∂wₙ]\n\nEach component ∂L/∂wᵢ answers:\n\"How does loss change if I tweak weight wᵢ while keeping all other weights the same?\""}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Update rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "wᵢ = wᵢ - learning_rate × ∂L/∂wᵢ  (for each weight)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes — Pitfalls to avoid"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistake"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Correction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Following positive gradient"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Follow NEGATIVE gradient (-∇L) to minimize loss"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Too large learning rate"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use small learning rate (0.001-0.01) to avoid overshooting"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not normalizing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Normalize gradient: `gradient = gradient /"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "gradient"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "` for consistent step size"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ignoring gradient magnitude"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient ≈ 0 → reached minimum; gradient very large → may need smaller learning rate"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Manual computation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use autograd (PyTorch/TensorFlow) for neural networks"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices — Proven approaches"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Use autograd frameworks"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\nmodel = NeuralNetwork()\nloss = compute_loss(model(x), y)\n\n# Automatic gradient computation\nloss.backward()\n\n# Gradients stored in model.parameters()\nfor param in model.parameters():\n    print(f\"Gradient: {param.grad}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Gradient clipping (prevent explosion)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.nn as nn\n\n# Clip gradients to max norm 1.0\nnn.utils.clip_grad_norm_(model.parameters(), max_norm=1.0)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Adaptive optimizers (Adam, RMSprop)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch.optim as optim\n\noptimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)\noptimizer.step()  # Update weights using adaptive learning rates"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. Check gradient magnitude"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "for param in model.parameters():\n    if param.grad is not None:\n        grad_norm = param.grad.norm()\n        print(f\"Gradient magnitude: {grad_norm}\")\n        \n        if grad_norm > 10:\n            print(\"Warning: Gradient explosion!\")\n        if grad_norm < 0.001:\n            print(\"Warning: Gradient vanishing!\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient = vector of partial derivatives"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": ∇f = [∂f/∂x₁, ∂f/∂x₂,...]"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Points uphill"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Gradient points in direction of steepest increase"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Negative gradient points downhill"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Follow -∇L to minimize loss"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Magnitude = steepness"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": |∇f| = rate of fastest increase"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient descent"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "w = w - learning_rate × ∇L"}, {"type": "text", "text": " updates parameters downhill"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convergence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Gradient → 0 signals optimal solution"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Neural networks"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Each ∂L/∂wᵢ tells how loss changes when weight wᵢ changes"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use autograd"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": PyTorch/TensorFlow compute gradients automatically"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient clipping"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Prevent explosion with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "clip_grad_norm_()"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adaptive optimizers"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Adam adjusts learning rates per parameter"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, gradients are absolutely fundamental: every training step, every backpropagation computation, and every parameter update relies on the gradient to tell the model exactly how to adjust millions or billions of parameters to reduce error and improve predictions."}]}]}}